A HTTP proxy server that only handles correctly the `CONNECT` verb to the
server `https://127.0.0.1:4433` where it create a TLS with a valid certificate
signed by a generated CA certificate and returns `HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request`.

The is just a project to get familiar with the OpenSSL libary and the HTTP
proxy tunnelling protocol. It is not intended to be a useful proxy server.

    // create ca key 
    openssl genrsa -des3 -out ca.key 2048

    // create ca pem, password=password  
    openssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key ca.key -sha256 -days 1024 -out ca.pem

    // build the server
    make

    // run the servwer
    ./server

    // test the server
    curl https://127.0.0.1 --cacert ca.pem --proxy localhost:4433 
